  "title": "BIM Manager",
  "description": "<p>· Set up BIM models based on office standards at the beginning of a project</p>\n<p>· Guide the project team on correct modelling practices and audit the project model/s from time to time</p>\n<p>· Use BIM (Building Information Modelling) to perform drawing and design work</p>\n<p>· Develop documentation and guide staff to make BIM e-submissions to the Authorities using Autodesk Revit (BIM) software</p>\n<p>· Manage process of exchange, collaboration and coordination of BIM Data with consultants and contractors</p>\n<p>· Coordinate and liaise with project and construction team on submissions, updates or changes, and checking for clashes with other disciplines</p>\n<p>· Perform interference checking in Autodesk Navisworks and maintain proper documentation of clash detection report</p>\n<p>· Review and update office BIM processes and related digitalisation processes as part of a BIM panel to constantly improve work standards, processes and techniques</p>\n<p>· Assist to plan, manage and maintain the BIM data to meet project deliverable requirements</p>\n<p>· Assist in maintaining BIM standards and workflow in accordance to company standards</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>· Minimum Diploma in Architecture/Structure/Mechanical or equivalent with relevant experience. Or BCA Specialist Diploma in Building Information Modelling (BIM)</p>\n<p>· Minimum 5 years of experience in BIM and use of Revit and Navisworks for Architectural works</p>\n<p>· Well versed in construction documentation using Autodesk Revit software and BIM 360</p>\n<p>· Experience of authority BIM e-submission</p>\n<p>· Scripting experience an added advantage</p>\n<p>· Great interpersonal skills and helpful attitude are essential</p>",
